title: Led Zeppelin - 1969.03.19 London, Maida Vale Studio
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1969.03.19 London, Maida Vale Studio   

MARCH 19 - RHYTHM & BLUES, STUDIO 4, MAIDA VALE, LONDON, ENGLAND 
(WEDNESDAY, recording session between 5:30pm and 9pm) 

Source: Complete superb professional pre-FM radio recording.
Details: The tape is an excellent radio master.

Tracklist:
01 - Alexis Korner Intro
02 - What Is And What Should Never Be
03 - More Chat
04 - I Can't Quit You Baby
05 - More Chat
06 - You Shook Me
07 - Sunshine Woman

Comments:  
What makes this tape interesting is the group's attempt to the song called 
Sunshine Woman. It shares the "I've got a mortgage on my body/I've got a 
lean on my soul" and "When she walks/she walks just like a willow tree" 
lyrics and is an interesting coincidence Plant recycles those lyrics since 
Rod Stewart was using them in the Jeff Beck Group at the same time
